          "order": 3,
          "title": "NODE CONFIG HELL",
          "summary": "Many production-ready Next.js projects require almost 30 configuration files to run. Having so many configurations can hinder developer productivity. The problem arises from the unopinionated nature of the JavaScript ecosystem, where the same code needs to be adaptable to various frameworks and tools. However, there are solutions with zero configs and smart defaults.",
