          "title": "SCROLLBARS ARE BECOMING A PROBLEM",
          "summary": "The shrinking size of scrollbars in modern software interfaces poses challenges for individuals with fine motor control problems or those who rely on alternative input methods. This author provides a comprehensive overview of the problem across various platforms and offers valuable insights into the need for user-configurable options to address it. They provide configuration tips for Firefox, but found Chrome hard to configure.",
